cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with 3D pose estimation from a single image. It also involves deep learning techniques, which suggests it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) category. The use of stereo reconstruction and multi-view consistency could place it in the robotics (cs.RO) category. The paper also involves data-driven regularization, which could suggest it belongs to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. Finally, the evaluation on a large dataset could suggest it belongs to the graphics (cs.GR) category.
